    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>+ In Dei nomine. Anno domini nostri Iesu Christi natalis millesimo centesimo
                        XLVI, tempore <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/409">Eugenii</persName>
                        <rs key="#Popes">pape</rs> et <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/126">Chouradi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">regis</rs>, die mensis decenbris nono, indictione
                        VIIII. In loco qui dicitur <placeName key="#Rural_communities"
                            >Costa</placeName>, iuxta <rs key="#Rivers">flumen</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers">Adticis</placeName>. Controversia fuit inter
                            <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/3747">Paulum</persName>, <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abbatem</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Abbots" ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sancte Marie</orgName>
                        de <placeName ref="#places/4179">Ponposia</placeName>, et <persName
                            key="#Priors #Monasteries" ref="#people/3716">Madebelatum</persName>,
                            <rs key="#Priors">priorem</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Priors" ref="#juridical_persons/2075">Sancti
                            Cipriani</orgName> de <placeName key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/914"
                            >Venecia</placeName>, cella <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/2001"
                            >Sancti Benedicti in Lairone</orgName>, et fuit in audientia, datis
                        pignoribus, iudicum <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Iohannes/iudex/de Vado">Iohannis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudicis</rs> de <placeName>Vado</placeName> et <persName
                            key="#Judge"><name ref="Adelgerius/de Sancta Cruce"
                            >Adegerii</name></persName> de <placeName>Sancta Cruce</placeName>,
                        precepto domini <persName key="#Cardinals"><name ref="Wido/cardinalis"
                                >Guidonis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Cardinals">cardinalis</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cardinals" ref="#juridical_persons/1100">ecclesie
                            Romane</orgName>. Petebat enim predictus abbas adversus predictum
                        priorem totam scilicet possessionem predicte Coste quam predictum
                        monasterium Sancti Cipriani tenebat, et <rs key="#Witness">testes</rs>
                        predictus abbas producebat. E contra prior prenominatus respondebat per se
                        et per suos auctores, <rs key="#childOf">filios</rs> quondam <rs
                            key="#Marquis/duke">marchionis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Marquis/duke #parentOf" ref="#people/3533"
                            >Fulconis</persName>, per longiora tempora quiete possedisse et
                        quamplures testes ex his in placito proferebat. Hinc inde quampluribus
                        dictis rationibus, lis taliter finem accepit, quod prescripti iudices, qui
                        pignora habebant, et per rationem et per convenientiam voluntate et consensu
                        utriusque partis iusserint ut predictus prior daret <rs key="#Price">XVcim
                            libras denariorum Veronensium</rs> supradicto abbati, et abbas cum <rs
                            key="#Advocatus">advocato</rs> suo <persName ref="#people/3748"
                            >Saliinguerra</persName> fecit finem perpetualiter prescripto priori
                        suisque successoribus de tota illa possessione qua dicitur Costa, sicuti
                        continetur in cartula Sancti Cipriani, infra hec latera: unum latus fiumen
                        Attisscis, salium latu <rs key="#Canals">fossa</rs> que dicitur
                            <placeName>Gaibo</placeName>, uno caput
                        <placeName>Policinus</placeName>, de subto <placeName>Rametelli</placeName>,
                        alio capite <persName><name ref="Albarus/de Publicano"
                            >Albarus</name></persName> de Publicano. Preter <rs key="#Lakes"
                            >lacum</rs> unum, <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">quem
                            debent piscare</rs>
                        <rs key="#Rural_communities">homines <placeName
                                key="#Villas #Rural_communities" ref="#places/4181"><rs
                                    key="#Villas" ref="#places/4180">ville</rs>
                            Martiane</placeName></rs> per abbatem tantum et homines predicte Coste,
                        iure Sancti Cipriani tantum et non alii communiter. Et hoc totum firmatum
                        est per abbatem, sub pena <rs key="#Penalty">centum librarum denariorum
                            Verone</rs>. Ad hec fuerunt testes presentes: <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #siblingOf #Witness" ref="#people/3749"
                            >Bonifatius</persName> et <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #siblingOf #Witness" ref="#people/3750"
                            >Albertus</persName>
                        <rs key="#siblingOf">germani</rs> marchiones, predictus Saliinguerra,
                            <persName key="#childOf #Witness" ref="#people/3751">Albertus</persName>
                        filius quondam <persName key="#Count #parentOf" ref="#people/3785"
                            >Maltraversi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs>, <persName key="#Advocatus #Witness"><name
                                ref="Alferius/advocatus Ferariensis">Alferus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Advocatus #Witness"><name
                                ref="Bernardus/advocatus Ferariensis">Bernardus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Advocatus #Witness"><name
                                ref="Rodulfus/advocatus Ferariensis">Rodulfus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Advocatus #Witness"><name
                                ref="Gherardus/advocatus Ferariensis">Gerardus</name></persName>
                        advocati <placeName key="#Advocatus" ref="#places/80"
                            >Ferarienses</placeName>, <persName key="#Advocatus #Witness"><name
                                ref="Heinricus/advocatus/de Urbana">Henricus</name></persName> de
                            <placeName ref="#places/4135">Urbana</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Advocatus #Witness"><name ref="Iohannes/advocatus/de Monte Silice"
                                >Iohannes</name></persName> de <placeName ref="#places/918">Monte
                            Silice</placeName> advocati, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Azo/de Policina">Aço</name></persName> de Policina, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Peregrinus/de Remedello"
                            >Peregrinus</name></persName> de Ramedello, <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Beritius/de Nitiche">Beriçus</name></persName> de
                        Nithiche, <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Albericus/Musa de Bove"
                                >Albericus Musa de Bove</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Causus">Caucus</name></persName> quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Agnellus">Agnelli</name></persName> et alii quam plures. Et ego
                            <persName key="#Notary #Writer"><name ref="Angelbertus"
                                >Angelbertus</name></persName> Ferariensis <rs key="#Notary"
                            >notarius</rs> predicta supradictorum iudicum <rs key="#Writer"
                            >scripsi</rs> hec omnia pro memoria retinenda. </ab>
